I thought I got to the substance of your argument quite well, and prefer not to drone on with a million quotes. If you want to press your argument further you will need to construct an argument as to why "putting someone in the position" obligates you to sustain their life, and when doing so you may want to examine the consequences of that position, to see if you can apply it consistently.You put it theretherefore you are responsible for itisn't, in itself, an argument.